{"parse":{"title":"Evandro Chagas Institute","pageid":30025172,"revid":849652663,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Evandro Chagas Institute</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Portuguese_language\" title=\"Portuguese language\">Portuguese</a> <i><b>Instituto Evandro Chagas</b></i>, or <b>IEC</b>) is a <a href=\"/wiki/Non-profit_organization\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Non-profit organization\">non-profit organization</a> which promotes <a href=\"/wiki/Public_health\" title=\"Public health\">public health</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Brazil\" title=\"Brazil\">Brazil</a> named after <a href=\"/wiki/Evandro_Chagas\" title=\"Evandro Chagas\">Evandro Chagas</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Research\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Research</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Evandro_Chagas_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In the 1940s fisherman Henrique Penna from the <a href=\"/wiki/Rockefeller_Foundation\" title=\"Rockefeller Foundation\">Rockefeller Foundation</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Rio_de_Janeiro\" title=\"Rio de Janeiro\">Rio de Janeiro</a> reported that he had discovered cases of <a href=\"/wiki/Leishmaniasis\" title=\"Leishmaniasis\">leishmaniasis</a> in Brazil's countryside.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (December 2010)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>  The disease had not been previously detected in Brazil, and as a response, <a href=\"/wiki/Carlos_Chagas\" title=\"Carlos Chagas\">Carlos Chagas</a> of the <a href=\"/wiki/Oswaldo_Cruz_Institute\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Oswaldo Cruz Institute\">Oswaldo Cruz Institute</a> organized a commission leishmaniasis to be headed by his son Evandro Chagas.\n</p><p>In 1938 this commission became the <i>Instituto de Pathologia Experimental do Norte</i>, or Northern Institution for Experimental Pathology (IPEN), with a mission to study leishmaniasis and other regional diseases. In 1940 Evandro Chagas died in a plane crash. To acknowledge his work as a scientist, the government changed the name of the former IPEN into the Evandro Chagas Institute.<sup id=\"cite_ref-history_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-history-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Research\">Research</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Evandro_Chagas_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Research\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The IEC organized local volunteers to participate in the <a href=\"/wiki/IPrEx\" title=\"IPrEx\">iPrEx</a> study, which was a <a href=\"/wiki/Clinical_trial\" title=\"Clinical trial\">clinical trial</a> testing the efficacy of a drug used as a <a href=\"/wiki/Pre-exposure_prophylaxis\" title=\"Pre-exposure prophylaxis\">pre-exposure prophylaxis</a> against HIV infection.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Evandro_Chagas_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-history-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-history_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.iec.pa.gov.br/en/iechistory.htm\">\"History\"</a>. <i>About IEC</i>. Evandro Chagas Institute<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">12 December</span> 2010</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=About+IEC&amp;rft.atitle=History&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.iec.pa.gov.br%2Fen%2Fiechistory.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEvandro+Chagas+Institute\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Evandro_Chagas_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.iec.pa.gov.br/\">Evandro Chagas Institute</a></li></ul>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata pla